node.text:
Retired flight attendant Paul Veneto of Braintree Massachusetts has successfully completed a 220 mile trek from Boston to NYC pushing a beverage cart ... a tribute to flight attendants and passengers who lost their lives 20 years ago today. Funds raised will be split between donations to families of those who lost their life & Power Forward 25, an organization that helps those struggling with addiction, a battle he knows first-hand. Swipe right for video of trek.
Let's congratulate @pauliespush ... you're amazing Paulie!!! You make us all proud. 🇺🇸 ❤

node.text:
Henry Ray Fischbach, a jazz singer started to feel faint during a performance last July and fell to the ground mid-performance--he was having a cardiac arrest. Medical professionals said he died twice before being brought to life.
"We could see he was on the floor and on his side," said Dr. Matthew Simhon, an orthopedic surgery resident at NewYork-Presbyterian/Columbia University Irving Medical Center. "His skin was very blue. We didn’t feel any pulse. He wasn’t breathing whatsoever."
Simhon, Dr. Andrew Luzzi, who is also an orthopedic surgery resident at NewYork-Presbyterian/Columbia University Irving Medical Center, and Dr. Marc Dyrszka, a spine surgeon affiliated with NewYork-Presbyterian Och Spine, immediately performed chest compressions on Fischbach to bring him back to life for some 10 minutes until the ambulance arrived.  Fischbach is immensely grateful for these 3 heroes and dedicated a recent performance to the lifesavers.

Kate Spade ( @katespadeny )is celebrating the start of Fall this NYFW with a lifestyle Apple Orchard in the heart of New York City! The orchard will be open to the public starting today Wednesday, September 8th through Friday, September 10th (hours 8a-5p) allowing YOU to come by and pick your own apples on behalf of Kate Spade! It's in Gansevoort Plaza in The Meatpacking District.

🍎 TAG FRIENDS TO GO WITH... see you there 🍎 ❤. 

I was there this morning... gonna make my apple pie tonight 😊 #katespadepartner  #katespadeny
